# Phase 3D/3E follow-up: canonical URLs have no trailing slash (sitemap,
# canonical and hreflang all emit no-trailing), but Netlify's directory-index
# handling 301s /demo -> /demo/ etc. for dist/<path>/index.html files. The
# marker below is replaced at build time (scripts/prerender.ts) with one
# explicit "<path> <path>/index.html 200!" rewrite per prerendered route, so
# the canonical no-trailing URL serves 200 directly. The rules are FORCED —
# unforced 200 rewrites did not override the platform slash normalization on
# the deploy preview (the 301 fired before unforced rules). Safe to force:
# each rule matches one exact route path and targets that route's own index
# file. Deliberately excluded:
# "/" (a real root file) and "/en/" (its canonical includes the slash, so the
# Netlify /en -> /en/ 301 already lands on the canonical in one hop). /cs
# paths stay 301s above — never rewritten.
# @canonical-route-rewrites

# Phase 3D: SPA-only routes (no prerendered HTML file) keep serving the SPA
# shell with status 200. Every prerendered route is a real file in dist/ and
# is served before any rule below (no rule below is forced with "!", and
# Netlify serves existing files before non-forced redirects).
/projekty/*   /spa-shell.html   200
/brozura-hotely   /spa-shell.html   200
/brozura-zdravotnictvi   /spa-shell.html   200
/brozura-autoservisy   /spa-shell.html   200

# Story Lab (Phase 4A §3 — EXPERIMENT BRANCH ONLY, never on main): lab routes
# serve the SPA shell; the lab page itself emits noindex,nofollow.
/__story-lab/*   /spa-shell.html   200

# Phase 3D: hard 404 for everything else — must stay last. Replaces the old
# "/* /index.html 200" SPA fallback (documented adjustment, plan §5.6): all
# valid routes are either prerendered files, 301s above, or the explicit
# SPA rewrites above, so the catch-all can finally return a real 404 status.
/*   /404.html   404
